<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imregionalmax3" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imregionalmax3</refname><refpurpose>Find regional maxima in a 3D volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imregionalmax3(volume); out = imregionalmax3(volume, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Input 3-D scalar volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para>3-D connectivity, commonly <literal>6</literal> or <literal>26</literal>. Default is <literal>26</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Boolean volume marking regional maxima.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para>Marks strict local maxima using 6-, 18-, or 26-connectivity. Flat plateaus are intentionally excluded by this lightweight implementation.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = im2double(rgb2gray(imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_smarties.png"))));
volume = cat(3, image, image + 0.2, image);
maxima = imregionalmax3(volume, 26);
imshow(max(maxima, 3));]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imregionalmax">imregionalmax</link></member><member><link linkend="imregionprops3">imregionprops3</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
